U.K. stocks retreated as the shares
of Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc, Lloyds Banking Group Plc
and Legal & General Group Plc dropped.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index lost 0.3 percent to 5,715.16
at 11:57 a.m. in London after earlier climbing as much as 0.9
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
